<li><a href="Muhammad_bin_Yahya_al-Ninowy" title="Muhammad bin Yahya al-Ninowy">Muhammad bin Yahya al-Ninowy</a> (b. 1966) – United States</li>
<li><a href="Zaid_Shakir" title="Zaid Shakir">Zaid Shakir</a> (b. 1956) – United States</li>
</ul>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Sufism&action=edit&section=40.php.html" title="Edit section: South Asia">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="South_Asia">South Asia</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="Saheb_Qibla_Fultali" title="Saheb Qibla Fultali">Abdul Latif Chowdhury Fultali</a> (1913–2008) – Bangladesh</li>
<li><a href="Ahmed_Raza_Khan_Barelvi" title="Ahmed Raza Khan Barelvi">Ahmed Raza Khan</a> (1856–1921) – India</li>
<li><a href="Akhtar_Raza_Khan" title="Akhtar Raza Khan">Akhtar Raza Khan</a> (b. 1943) – India</li>
<li><a href="Meher_Ali_Shah" title="Meher Ali Shah">Meher Ali Shah</a> (1859–1937) – India</li>
<li><a href="Muhammad_Tahir-ul-Qadri" title="Muhammad Tahir-ul-Qadri">Muhammad Tahir-ul-Qadri</a> (b. 1951) – Pakistan</li>
<li><a href="Qamaruzzaman_Azmi" title="Qamaruzzaman Azmi">Qamaruzzaman Azmi</a> (b. 1946) – India</li>
<li><a href="Syed_Waheed_Ashraf" title="Syed Waheed Ashraf">Syed Waheed Ashraf</a> (b. 1933) – India</li>
</ul>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Sufism&action=edit&section=41.php.html" title="Edit section: Eastern and Central Asia">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Eastern_and_Central_Asia">Eastern and Central Asia</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="Muhammad_Abdul_Aleem_Siddiqi" title="Muhammad Abdul Aleem Siddiqi">Muhammad Abdul Aleem Siddiqi</a> (1892–1954) – Singapore</li>
<li><a href="Muhammad_Ma_Jian" title="Muhammad Ma Jian">Muhammad Ma Jian</a> (1906–1978) – China</li>
<li><a href="Syed_Muhammad_Naquib_al-Attas" title="Syed Muhammad Naquib al-Attas">Syed Muhammad Naquib al-Attas</a> (b. 1931) – Malaysia</li>
</ul>
